I really liked this one.

Maybe it's not the longest or most developed SCP ever added to this site, but I found it really interesting.

Great characterization of the entity, although this was quite a humorous character it fitted the article well.

Also I liked the idea of the older gods getting together and forming some form of business, made the divine appear mundane which is a welcome relief from all of the omnipotent gods and god weapons that seem to be all too common here.

+1







