Very good. Nothing here was over-the-top: -A was humorous, but not wacky; the references were well-chosen for embedding this piece in the Foundation universe, and didn't feel like thoughtless name-dropping; and you provided enough exposition and development to satisfy basic curiosity, but left a good number of details to the reader's imagination. Measured and interesting. Like it a lot.







